RESPONSIBILITIES
Responsibilities will include:
Ensure a high-quality client on-boarding processes from a documentation standpoint, across all asset classes Undertaking administrative data and documentation management work Responsible for the life cycle of client information by reviewing account documentation Responsible for maintaining static data and ensuring the accuracy and completeness of all sourced data Direct liaison with, and support to mainly internal clients regarding all document processing matters including the advisory and all other partners including other departments within operations, Legal and Compliance etc.
EDUCATION
For this role you will ideally have tertiary education. SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE
At least 3 years of experience in Client on-Boarding function within an FX Brokerage or Banking institution In-depth knowledge of client documentation/ KYC/ AML requirements
As you will be dealing with forms in both English and Arabic, fluency in written Arabic is a must.
